  "body": "Our HTTP RPC endpoint currently accepts requests on all request verbs (https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/15490#issuecomment-344618139). Perhaps we shouldn't do so blindly to avoid weird combinations that could potentially circumvent CORS? Would be nice to drop support for PUT and DELETE altogether, and think a bit about the others.",
